ray of live programming, such as coverage of missions, events (spacewalks, media interviews, educational broadcasts), press conferences and rocket launches. \n\nIn the United States, NASA Television's Public and Media channels are MPEG-2 digital C-band signals carried by DVB-S2/8PSK modulation on satellite Galaxy 13, transponder 15, at 127 degrees west longitude. Downlink frequency is 4009.00 MHz, horizontal polarization, with a data rate of 36.225 Mbps, symbol rate of 15.000 Msps, and 5/6 FEC. A Digital Video Broadcast (DVB-S2) compliant Integrated Receiver Decoder (IRD) is needed for reception.","commandRuns":[{"startIndex":338,"length":22,"onTap":{"innertubeCommand":{"clickTrackingParams":"CPcBEM2rARgBIhMIjNKv-8uDlAMV6qorBh0t0zkjSPjzjMrGsv6q2wHKAQRgf5Fi","commandMetadata":{"webCommandMetadata":{"url":"https://www.youtube.com/redirect?event=video_description\u0026redir_token=QUFFLUhqbTl3QjdpUEdjSnNnNUQ5Ul9sTmN4cmh6V1FlQXxBQ3Jtc0tsalM4MFRSQkpLV3UwRmRIZFJtS0hOdklDNTI0bmpRbzVDMk10cnVpWi1MOGxFWjBuRWxMMERCUUw4ME5JM1Rmc3ZjYS1VaDZNS0JUSEM3SzJfdEc1VmRlWlBMLUtvLWhrb242UHEtMFc1YWJxWExkVQ\u0026q=https%3A%2F%2Fplus.nasa.gov%2F\u0026v=21X5lGlDOfg","webPageType":"WEB_PAGE_TYPE_UNKNOWN","rootVe":83769}},"urlEndpoint":{"url":"https://www.youtube.com/redirect?event=video_description\u0026redir_token=QUFFLUhqbTl3QjdpUEdjSnNnNUQ5Ul9sTmN4cmh6V1FlQXxBQ3Jtc0tsalM4MFRSQkpLV3UwRmRIZFJtS0hOdklDNTI0bmpRbzVDMk10cnVpWi1MOGxFWjBuRWxMMERCUUw4ME5JM1Rmc3ZjYS1VaDZNS0JUSEM3SzJfdEc1VmRlWlBMLUtvLWhrb242UHEtMFc1YWJxWExkVQ\u0026q=https%3A%2F%2Fplus.nasa.gov%2F\u0026v=21X5lGlDOfg","target":"TARGET_NEW_WINDOW","nofollow":true}}}}],"styleRuns":[{"startIndex":0,"length":79,"styleRunExtensions":{"styleRunColorMapExtension":{"colorMap":[{"key":"USER_INTERFACE_THEME_DARK","value":4294967295},{"key":"USER_INTERFACE_THEME_LIGHT","value":4279440147}]}},"fontFamilyName":"Roboto"},{"startIndex":79,"length":13,"fontName":"Roboto-Medium","weightLabel":"FONT_WEIGHT_BOLD","styleRunExtensions":{"styleRunColorMapExtens